# Copy to .env.local. This app runs on port 3001 by default.

# Supabase (same project as apps/web; local: `supabase status` → API URL + anon key)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54331
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# Site URL for this app (used in docs / optional client checks)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3001

# --- GitHub OAuth (Sign in with GitHub) ---
#
# Hosted Supabase:
# 1. Dashboard → Authentication → Providers → GitHub: enable, add Client ID + Secret from GitHub.
# 2. Dashboard → Authentication → URL configuration:
#    - Site URL: your deployed developer portal origin, e.g. https://developer.example.com
#    - Redirect URLs: add https://your-origin/auth/callback (and http://localhost:3001/auth/callback for local)
#
# Local Supabase (`supabase start`):
# 1. GitHub → Settings → Developer settings → OAuth Apps → New.
#    - Authorization callback URL MUST be the Supabase Auth callback (not your Next app):
#        http://127.0.0.1:54331/auth/v1/callback
# 2. In repo root `supabase/config.toml`, set [auth.external.github] enabled = true.
# 3. Put the SAME variable names in the **repository root** `.env` (not only `supabase/.env`):
#    SUPABASE_AUTH_EXTERNAL_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID / SUPABASE_AUTH_EXTERNAL_GITHUB_SECRET
#    The Supabase CLI substitutes `env(...)` in config.toml from the **root** `.env`.
# 4. Run: supabase stop && supabase start
# 3. Redirect URLs for the *app* are already listed under [auth] additional_redirect_urls
#    for http://localhost:3001/auth/callback and http://127.0.0.1:3001/auth/callback
